title: Tender Submission — Lusail Marina District Cooling Plant (Civil & MEP Package)
summary: Bill of Quantities, commercial summary and authorization · valid until 2026-08-30
meta: | type: tender | ref: TND-2026-088 | client: Lusail Real Estate Development Company | prepared-by: Al-Mirqab Construction & Engineering W.L.L. | currency: QAR | due: 2026-08-15 | theme: corporate

toc:

section: 1. Tender Particulars

text: This submission responds to invitation-to-tender ITT-LUSAIL-2026-031 for the construction of a district cooling plant building and associated MEP installation at Plot DC-4, Marina District, Lusail. All rates are firm and inclusive of labour, materials, plant, supervision, wastage and contractor's overheads, exclusive of VAT.

contact: Al-Mirqab Construction & Engineering W.L.L. | role: Tenderer | email: tenders@almirqab.qa | tel: +974 4012 7700 | cr: CR-118842 | vat: VAT-300884512
contact: Lusail Real Estate Development Company | role: Employer | email: procurement@lusail.qa
contact: Aurecon Qatar W.L.L. | role: Consultant / Engineer | email: pm@aurecon.qa

def: BOQ | meaning: Bill of Quantities — the priced schedule of measured works forming the contract sum
def: PC Sum | meaning: Prime Cost sum — a budgetary allowance for materials selected by the Engineer post-award
def: Provisional Sum | meaning: An allowance for work not yet fully defined, expended only on the Engineer's instruction

cite: QCS 2014 — Qatar Construction Specifications | section: Series 5 (Concrete) & Series 21 (MEP)

assumption: Site is handed over free of obstructions and dewatered to -1.5 m | owner: Employer
assumption: Rates exclude any escalation in steel rebar beyond 2026-08-30 | owner: Tenderer
exclusion: VAT, customs duties on free-issue items, and third-party utility connection charges | basis: priced separately by Employer

